<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Water Supply: Activating Packages</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Water Supply: Activating Packages</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This model uses the River and Well packages so those two packages need to be activated.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model|MODFLOW Packages and Programs...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to display the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Packages_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. &#160;Use the splitter control between the tree control on the left and the rest of the dialog box to see more or less of the tree control. &#160;Check the check boxes for the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">River</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Well</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> packages which are found on the tree control under </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Boundary conditions|Specified flux</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Boundary conditions|Head-dependent flux</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. Click </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">OK</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to close the dialog box.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
